;W[en]LB[ek:1][el:2][fl:3][fm:4][gl:5][en:6]C[Dia.1 White 6 is good shape

{\colortbl ;\red255\green0\blue0;}
Usually in Baduk books they encourage us to play the diagonal move of Black 1, right?  White will push out with 2, then Black will hit the head of two stones with 3.

When White plays 4 we come to an important juncture.  We can't play a weak move like Black 5, it has no power.  When White plays the tiger's mouth at 6, it makes good shape for him.\cf1\b   Now it's not clear where Black should play.\cf0\b0

\lang1042\f1\fs18

