(;AW[cf][qh][dl][el][fm][jn][gp][np][nq]AB[dd][fd][jd][pd][dj][jj][pj][qj][ek][fl][dn][pn][dp][jp][pp][oq]LB[ci:A][co:B]
;B[em]
;W[bl]LB[em:1][bl:2][ci:A][co:B]C[Dia.2 Complex

{\colortbl ;\red255\green0\blue0;}
In response to the marked White stone, Black should cut straight away.  Even then, White can jump at 2 and this rather hurts for Black.

Next, White A and B are matbogi.  Black should get a good result if he responds correctly, but \cf1 since this is complex \cf0 it is easy for the weaker player to make a mistake.  Simple is best.

\lang1042\f1\fs18

