;B[ei]LB[eg:1][ch:2][ei:3][cf:][ch:B]CR[dl]C[Dia.3 An easy to understand way to attack

{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
Black's large knight's move at 1 aiming to cover the White stone is an easy to understand move.  So we don't directly respond to the marked White stone, instead we start a fight on the other side.

When White plays 2 Black plays the diagonal of 3 to stay connected and keep up the pressure.\cf1\b This is a simple and safe way to attack.\cf0\b0   White is in for a long, bitter struggle.
\lang1042\f1\fs18
